<L>__{exterior the micmac burying ground, louis and jud's pov}
<A>__{the top of this hill or bluff is rocky and bare, but there are a number of rocky piles. but for every pile of rocks we can see, there are ten littered heaps, as if the neat piles had been burst apart. there's a shape to all of this, and it is the shape of the pet sematary: concentric circles. sound: the wind, blowing ceaselessly.}
